Apparently the SH4 domain regulates the activity of the CD domain in a negative way, inhibiting. But then, we should still be able to predict that, right? Well, for example, if you introduce a stop sign in SH4, it will be bad for the whole protein. So it's not easily predictable. Also, on SH4 standard errors are pretty high, so I imagine replicates might be bad.
